BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Timber! Understanding the Timber Rattlesnake\, Brown County State 
 Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260522T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260522T150000
UID:a8b2e78e669d47ada47d903781f9751a@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Come to the Nature Center for an up close and personal look In
 diana&#39\;s most venomous and most misunderstood snake! Learn about the h
 istory of timber rattlesnakes\, including how this animal became an Americ
 an symbol in the late 1700s. Learn how over a million visitors a year safe
 ly share the state park with these animals. We&#39\;ll also discuss venom\
 , how it works and is delievered\, and how Indiana&#39\;s venomous snakes 
 compare to the rest of the world! At the end\, we will feed the timber rat
 tlesnake a live mouse. Please be aware this program involves live animals.
  A live snake feeding may not be suitable for all guests\, particuarly chi
 ldren. Guests will have an opportunity to leave the program before the fee
 ding\, if they choose to do so. The program room has seating for about 45 
 people maximum. On busy days\, it is wise to arrive early!
LOCATION:Brown County State Park\, Nature Center\, 1405 S.R. 46 W\, Nashvi
 lle\, IN 
URL:https://on.in.gov/browncountysp
X-SOURCE:Brown County State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Full Moon Hike\, Brown County State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260530T210000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260530T220000
UID:236ea49f77e767cec55a86818a268f83@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Join a park naturalist for a guided night hike on the Salt Cre
 ek Trail! The Full Moon is the brightest night of the month\, leading to i
 nteresting views along the creek. Learn about May&#39\;s second full moon 
 this year\, the Blue Moon. The Salt Creek Trail is rated very easy\, but s
 hould be considered moderate in the dark. The trail has some minor slopes\
 , a short stretch of lawn\, and possible wet or icy spots depending on wea
 ther. Our route is&nbsp\; about 2 miles total and will take about an hour 
 to complete. Please do not bring pets on night hikes. Red flashlights are 
 preferred for night vision and can be loaned to hikers on request.
LOCATION:Brown County State Park\, Olympic Pool parking lot\, 1405 S.R. 46
  W\, Nashville\, IN 
URL:https://on.in.gov/BrownCountySP
X-SOURCE:Brown County State Park
END:VEVENT
