BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mothing in Indiana\, Brown County State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260725T210000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260725T230000
UID:491dd54e89d059f890500cc818459e1e@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Moths may conjure images of drab and brown insects fluttering 
 at our porch lights\, but with over 2\,300 species recorded in the state\,
  there&rsquo\;s much to learn about these mostly-nocturnal fliers. We&rsqu
 o\;ll have a few lights set up to attract moths to a white sheet so we can
  view the stunning diversity of these little gems. This is an excellent pr
 ogram for families\, and children of all ages are encouraged to attend. Br
 ing a flashlight for best viewing of moths on the sheet.
LOCATION:Brown County State Park\, Nature Center\, Friends' Shelter\, 1405
  S.R. 46 W\, Nashville\, IN 
URL:https://on.in.gov/BrownCountySP
X-SOURCE:Brown County State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Full Moon Hike\, Brown County State Park
